The paper deals with the problem of identifying heavy hitters and hierarchical heavy hitters in real-time for applications such as load balancing, traffic engineering, and attack mitigation. This problem is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including network infrastructure (cs.NI), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). However, given the focus on network traffic analysis and optimization, cs.NI and cs.CR are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.SI, and cs.DM.
